cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the definition and processing of clauses in Ukrainian text, which falls under the domain of natural language processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the Menzerath-Altmann law is a statistical law that can be applied to syntactic structures, and machine learning techniques can be used to analyze and model such structures.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with automated processing of text, which is a common application of AI techniques.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper may have implications for the study of language and culture in Ukrainian society.
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also a less likely category, but the paper may be relevant for the development of tools and techniques for processing and analyzing large collections of Ukrainian texts.
